comments: Fox (SAC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Young (ATL) on the perimeter.
After the ball becomes loose, Young (ATL) moves forward into Sabonis' (SAC) body and initiates contact that allows Young to make contact with the ball.
Sabonis (SAC) is firming up over his left foot and absorbs the contact from Young (ATL) during the screen.
Bogdanovic (ATL) is already in Fox's (SAC) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Sabonis (SAC) is firming up over his right leg and absorbs the contact from Hunter (ATL) to his upper body.
Collins (ATL) moves forward into Fox's (SAC) body and delivers contact that affects his follow through.
Bogdanovic (ATL) establishes himself in Mitchell's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Murray (SAC) brings his hands forward and initiates contact with Young's (ATL) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) is firming up over his right leg when marginal contact occurs with Murray (ATL) during the pick.
Collins (ATL) is moving alongside Fox's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Hunter (ATL) moves towards Sabonis (SAC) and marginal contact occurs as Sabonis receives the pass.
Hunter (ATL) raises his arm up into Sabonis' (SAC) arm and initiates contact with Sabonis' arm prior to making any contact with the ball.
Murray (ATL) establishes himself in Mitchell's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Collins (ATL) brings his hands toward Huerter (SAC) and marginal contact occurs as Collins releases away to roll.

Replay review of the foul called on Huerter (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Huerter is moving to Young's (ATL) side when marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.  Atlanta had imminent possession of the ball, and play resumes with Atlanta retaining possession.
Sabonis (SAC) extends his forearm into Murray's (ATL) body and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) cleanly deflects the ball away from Fox (SAC).
Murray (ATL) goes to not through Fox's (SAC) space as they come together at the same spot in transition.
Okongwu (ATL) makes clean contact with the ball, and any ensuing contact with Fox's (SAC) arm is considered marginal.
Collins (ATL) legally contests Sabonis' (SAC) layup attempt.
